                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d465">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Baron <persName type="from">Fava</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Memorandum—Translation.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-10-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 25, 1900</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Royal Government of Italy having accepted the first propositions made by M.
                    Delcassé, and the powers being in accord as to principal points of the
                    proposition, the minister of the King at Pekin has been authorized to send to
                    the Chinese plenipotentiaries an identic note as soon as his colleagues shall
                    have received from their respective governments similar authorization.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">japan.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
